1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,200
Science has a clearer story about context dependent memory than social media does.

2
00:00:05,200 --> 00:00:10,000
Imagine walking into a room and suddenly remembering something from last week.

3
00:00:10,000 --> 00:00:12,400
That’s context dependent memory at work.

4
00:00:12,400 --> 00:00:16,800
It means our memories are tied to the environment we’re in.

5
00:00:16,800 --> 00:00:19,600
Change the setting, and you may forget!

6
00:00:19,600 --> 00:00:25,600
Studies show that people recall information better in the same context where they learned it.

7
00:00:25,600 --> 00:00:30,400
So, if you study in a coffee shop, try testing in one.

8
00:00:30,400 --> 00:00:33,200
You might be amazed at your results!

9
00:00:33,200 --> 00:00:36,800
Want to dive deeper into how your brain works?

10
00:00:36,800 --> 00:00:39,600
Like and follow for more mind-blowing science!
